 President Muhammadu Buhari on Monday held a meeting with Rivers State Governor, Nyesom Wike at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. Wike arrived at about 2pm and went straight to the President’s office area. The governor, however, refused to disclose to newsmen the purpose of his visit to the Villa.
When contacted to comment on the visit of his principal, Wike’s Special Assistant, Simeon Nwakaudu, gave no response.